[C]And Jim would take Cindy to see New Orleans
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]The town folks would smile as they sat there alone
[C]Jim talked of the day he'd make Cindy his own
[G7]He saved his money to buy her a ring
[C]And take his sweet Cindy to see New Orleans
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[G7]One day a riverboat gambler chanced by
[C]And captured her heart with his sweet words and lies
[G7]He told her come with me and you'll be a queen
[C]So they left together to see New Orleans
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
